In a press briefing, Principal Deputy Attorney General Rob Hur and Acting Director of U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) Tom Homan discussed the efforts of the Department of Justice and ICE to combat criminal organizations like MS-13. Hur highlighted the Justice Department's aggressive efforts to dismantle MS-13, including the prosecution of gang members and the prioritization of violent crime and criminal immigration enforcement. Homan emphasized ICE's efforts to target and remove gang members, particularly those involved in violent crimes. He also stressed the importance of cooperation from local law enforcement and criticized sanctuary cities for hindering immigration enforcement.